 <p>Arch Mage Rhand Drago'Magica<br>
Officer of Lowland Elites<br>
Husband of Hebzibah Drago'Magica<br>
Antonius Bayle<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39733">Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=outofmana>OutOfMana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 11:52:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1698.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   prices on Xev</span><hr size=1> Saw the 61 pet going for 40k in the bazaar a couple of nights ago.  A lot of others go for 10-20k.  Not that it worries me too much - at 55 I figure by the time I get to 61 things will have calmed down.  If not, I'll stay at 60 for a bit and AAExp until I can pick up a few of the more significant 61 spells.<br>
<br>
More worrying is that Burnout IV does not seem to be available for love nor money.<br>
<br>
Still, some people have it worse.  The shammie malo spell was recently seen in the bazaar for 90k.  I picked up mala from a vendor for 43pp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaid2373>kaid2373</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 7:49:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1698.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://isaythere.solinus.com/swgwok_f_mb.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: prices on Xev</span><hr size=1> Spell pricing dosn't make much sense it is always pretty wild and due to the rarity of the parchments it will probably be a good long time before the post 60 spells drop to a reasonable leve.<br>
<br>
